The paper focuses on generating high fidelity 3D face avatars from a single image using deep neural networks and non-rigid deformation processes. This involves computer vision techniques such as image processing, 3D modeling, and texture mapping, which are all relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in virtual/augmented reality (VR/AR) and human-computer interaction, which are also relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep facial identity features learned from millions of facial images, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions applications in telepsychiatry and social networks, which are relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
